bug.short_desc: ocaml-ocamlnet-3.5.1-1.fc18 fails to build on ppc64

long_desc.thetext: Description of problem: ocaml-ocamlnet-3.5.1-1.fc18 fails to build on power: https://ppc.koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=638076 I believe this is the relevant section of the build log (full log will be attached): ocamlfind ocamlc -g -I ../../src/netsys -I +compiler-libs -package "pcre bigarray unix" -c netmappings_other.ml test ! -d mappings || tools/unimap_to_ocaml/unimap_to_ocaml \ -o netmappings_jp.pmap -pmap mappings/jis*.*map tools/unimap_to_ocaml/unimap_to_ocaml \ -o netmappings_jp.ml netmappings_jp.pmap Reading netmappings_jp.pmap Processing jis0212 (Heavy conflicts: 132 of 8192) Processing jis0208 (Heavy conflicts: 182 of 8192) Processing jis0201 (Heavy conflicts: 0 of 256) ocamlfind ocamlc -g -I ../../src/netsys -I +compiler-libs -package "pcre bigarray unix" -c netmappings_jp.ml ocamlc.opt got signal and exited rm nethtml_scanner.ml make[1]: *** [netmappings_jp.cmo] Error 2 make[1]: Leaving directory `/builddir/build/BUILD/ocamlnet-3.5.1/src/netstring' make: *** [all] Error 2
Be interesting to see what "signal" it got. If it segfaulted, what's the stack trace?

I reopen this problem as ocaml-ocamlnet never built on ppc64/ppc64le. Can you try raising the stack limit. The default on ppc64 is far too low to run OCaml programs. Example: http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/cgit/rpms/ocaml.git/tree/ocaml.spec#n217

You got it. I added changes in ocaml-ocamlnet.spec to raise stack limit in the same way it is done in ocaml.spec and ppc64/ppc64le builds are successful now. http://ppc.koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=3298369
This is fixed in Rawhide / OCaml 4.04. Also the raised stack limits no longer seem to be necessary.
